Don&#x27;t make it a tuple. A tuple indicates heterogenous data (a record), while a list indicates a sequence of data.<p>If nothing else, use lists because the syntax means it stays as a list even if you someday remove all but one option and forget to leave a comma, eg.<p><pre><code>  REASONS = [
    &#x27;leaves on the line&#x27;
  ]
</code></pre>
vs<p><pre><code>  REASONS = (
    &#x27;leaves on the line&#x27;
  )</code></pre>

I also had, we are delayed due to:<p>&quot;arriving early at the previous station&quot;
&
&quot;a Swan on the line&quot;
&
&quot;a passenger refusing to leave the first class carriage, that only has a standard ticket&quot; (police were called, delayed 25 mins)
